Udemy kurs: https://www.udemy.com/course/learn-kubernetes/?couponCode=KEEPLEARNING

Instalacja:

Instalacja aws cli 
https://aws.amazon.com/cli/

Instalacja winpty (for windows)

Instalacja kubectl (for windows: https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/tools/install-kubectl-windows/):
komenda:
curl.exe -LO "https://dl.k8s.io/v1.34.0/bin/windows/amd64/kubectl.exe.sha256"
Dodać Path: C:\Users\{user} do Environment variables 
Verify installation of kubectl kubectl version --client

Można użyć też k9s Kubernetes: CLI\https://k9scli.io/

Pycharm has this plugin for kubernetes (opcjonalnie)
https://github.com/redhat-developer/intellij-kubernetes

You can installed mini-kube on my windows machine to play with 
https://minikube.sigs.k8s.io/docs/start/?arch=%2Fwindows%2Fx86-64%2Fstable%2F.exe+download
and started it with hyperv 
minikube start --vm-driver=hyperv

to switch to minikube context kubectl config get-contexts
kubectl config use-context 

source <(kubectl completion bash)
echo "source <(kubectl completion bash)" >> ~/.bashrc

Kubectl autocomplete and k shorthand
echo 'alias k=kubectl' >>~/.bashrc
echo 'complete -F __start_kubectl ks' >>~/.bashrc
Kubectl autocomplete and k shorthand 
https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/quick-reference/#bash
